---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import AuthorByline from '../../components/AuthorByline.astro';

const title = "Chase Sapphire Preferred Break-Even: The Real Math on $95";
const description = "We ran the numbers on the Chase Sapphire Preferred $95 annual fee. Here's exactly what you need to spend to break even—and whether it's worth it.";
const publishDate = "2026-03-23";

// Article content as markdown string
const markdownContent = `The Chase Sapphire Preferred charges \$95 a year. You're paying for the privilege of using it. The question isn't whether it's a "good card"—the question is whether the math works for YOUR spending.

Most people apply for cards based on signup bonuses and brand reputation. That's backwards. The signup bonus is a one-time event. The annual fee is forever. If you can't break even on the fee through everyday spend, you're subsidizing Chase's profit margin.

## What You're Actually Paying For

The Chase Sapphire Preferred earns:
- **2X points** on travel and dining
- **1X points** on everything else
- Points are worth **1.25 cents each** when redeemed through Chase Travel

That 1.25-cent redemption rate is the key. It turns the card's earn rates into:
- **2.5% back** on travel and dining (2 points × 1.25¢)
- **1.25% back** on everything else (1 point × 1.25¢)

If you redeem points for cash back or transfer them to partners, the value changes. But Chase Travel redemption is the baseline the card is designed around.

## The Break-Even Calculation

To justify a \$95 annual fee, you need to earn at least \$95 more with this card than you would with a no-annual-fee alternative.

Let's compare to a flat **2% cashback card** (like the Citi Double Cash or Wells Fargo Active Cash):

| Spending Category | CSP Earn Rate | 2% Card Earn Rate | CSP Advantage |
|`;
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <article style="max-width: 48rem; margin: 0 auto; padding: 8rem 0 4rem;">
    <h1 style="font-size: 3rem; font-weight: 900; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--color-text); line-height: 1.1;">
      {title}
    </h1>

    <AuthorByline date={publishDate} />

    <div style="font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-top: 3rem;" set:html={markdownContent.split('\n\n').map(para => {
      // Handle headers
      if (para.startsWith('## ')) {
        const text = para.substring(3);
        return `<h2 style="font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text);">${text}</h2>`;
      }
      if (para.startsWith('### ')) {
        const text = para.substring(4);
        return `<h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 2rem 0 1rem; color: var(--color-text);">${text}</h3>`;
      }
      
      // Handle tables
      if (para.includes('|') && para.split('\n').length > 2) {
        const rows = para.split('\n').filter(r => r.trim());
        const headers = rows[0].split('|').map(h => h.trim()).filter(Boolean);
        const dataRows = rows.slice(2).map(row => row.split('|').map(cell => cell.trim()).filter(Boolean));
        
        let table = '<table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 2rem 0;"><thead><tr>';
        headers.forEach(h => {
          table += `<th style="text-align: left; padding: 0.75rem; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border); font-weight: 700;">${h}</th>`;
        });
        table += '</tr></thead><tbody>';
        dataRows.forEach(row => {
          table += '<tr>';
          row.forEach(cell => {
            // Convert **bold** in cells
            const formatted = cell.replace(/\*\*(.+?)\*\*/g, '<strong>$1</strong>');
            table += `<td style="padding: 0.75rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);">${formatted}</td>`;
          });
          table += '</tr>';
        });
        table += '</tbody></table>';
        return table;
      }
      
      // Handle lists
      if (para.match(/^- /m)) {
        const items = para.split('\n').filter(line => line.startsWith('- ')).map(line => {
          const text = line.substring(2).replace(/\*\*(.+?)\*\*/g, '<strong>$1</strong>');
          return `<li style="margin: 0.5rem 0;">${text}</li>`;
        }).join('');
        return `<ul style="margin: 1.5rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem;">${items}</ul>`;
      }
      
      // Regular paragraphs with inline formatting
      const formatted = para
        .replace(/\*\*(.+?)\*\*/g, '<strong>$1</strong>')
        .replace(/\*(.+?)\*/g, '<em>$1</em>')
        .split('\n').filter(Boolean).map(line => `<p style="margin: 1rem 0;">${line}</p>`).join('');
      return formatted;
    }).join('')}>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
